
Overview of noun showstopper

The noun showstopper has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                  
1. show-stopper, showstopper, stopper -- (an act so striking or impressive that the show must be delayed until the audience quiets down)
2. show-stopper, showstopper -- (something that is strikingly attractive or has great popular appeal; "she has a show-stopper of a smile"; "the brilliant orange flowers against the green foliage were a showstopper")
